The paper deals with image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of genetic algorithms (GA) for optimization is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could be relevant to graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the use of multi-objective optimization (MOO) suggests that the paper could also be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
